  "prompt": "How do I plan a trip to Antarctica?",
  "response": "Planning a trip to Antarctica requires careful preparation:\n\n1. Timing\n- Best time to visit: November to March (Antarctic summer)\n- Peak season: December to February\n\n2. Trip Options\n- Cruise ships\n- Expedition tours\n- Research station visits\n- Fly-cruise options\n\n3. Cost Considerations\n- Expensive: $5,000-$15,000+ per person\n- Includes transportation, accommodation, and expedition gear\n\n4. Preparation\n- Obtain proper cold weather clothing\n- Get travel insurance\n- Physical fitness check\n- Passport and necessary travel documents\n\n5. Choosing a Tour Operator\n- Look for experienced Antarctic tour companies\n- Check safety records and environmental practices\n- Compare itineraries and prices\n\n6. Travel Requirements\n- No visa required for most nationalities\n- Medical clearance recommended\n- Vaccinations and health precautions\n\n7. Packing Essentials\n- Extreme cold weather clothing\n- Waterproof layers\n- Thermal underwear\n- Sturdy boots\n- Sunglasses and sunscreen\n\n8. Transportation\n- Most trips depart from Ushuaia, Argentina\n- Some tours leave from New Zealand or Chile\n\n9. Activities\n- Wildlife viewing\n- Photography\n- Kayaking\n- Hiking\n- Scientific research observations",
